tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: The patient shows elevated creatinine, suggesting impaired renal function, and low total CO₂, which may indicate metabolic acidosis. Liver enzymes (ALP, ALT) are elevated, pointing to possible hepatobiliary involvement. Albumin is slightly high, and HDL cholesterol is mildly low. Other parameters are within normal limits. Recommend further evaluation of renal and liver function and assessment for underlying causes.
